TWO armed unknown men shot dead a gogo (70) and injured
another in two farmhouses at Lower Didiman in Kleinbulhoek. They allegedly approached one farmhouse where they shot and
injured a 55-year-old woman and thereafter proceeded to the second house where
they shot and killed the gogo. The motive for these attacks are unknown and will be
investigated. “The incident happened during the early hours of Monday
morning. Cases of murder and attempted murder has been opened for
investigation,” Captain Namhla Mdleleni. The police have appealed to the community for assistance in
tracking down the suspects who murdered one woman and shot another Anyone who can assist in the investigation is urged to
contact detective Warrant Officer Richard Frederick's at 0824418232 or the
Crime Stop line on 08600 10111.